Inline object/array/function props = new reference every render ŌåÆ child sees "new" prop ŌåÆ re-renders.

Common culprits:

```jsx
// Bad ŌĆö new object every render
<Child style={{ color: 'red' }} />

// Bad ŌĆö new function every render
<Child onClick={() => doThing()} />

// Bad ŌĆö new array every render
<Child items={data.filter(x => x.active)} />
```

Fixes:

```jsx
// Memoize objects/arrays
const style = useMemo(() => ({ color: 'red' }), []);
const items = useMemo(() => data.filter(x => x.active), [data]);

// Memoize callbacks
const onClick = useCallback(() => doThing(), []);
```

Then wrap child in `React.memo()` so it skips render when props unchanged by reference:

```jsx
const Child = React.memo(function Child({ style, onClick }) {
  return <button style={style} onClick={onClick}>click</button>;
});
```

**Debug tool:** React DevTools ŌåÆ Profiler ŌåÆ "Highlight updates when components render." Shows exactly what re-renders and why.

Debouncer on search input ŌåÆ avoid firing API call on every keystroke. User types "caveman" = 7 keystrokes. Without debounce = 7 requests. With debounce (e.g. 300ms) = 1 request after typing stops.

**Why it matters:**
- Less server load
- No wasted network requests for partial strings like "ca", "cav", "cave"
- Avoids race conditions where "cav" response arrives after "caveman" response, showing stale results
- Smoother UX ŌĆö no flickering results while typing

**Basic pattern:**
```js
